User stories - Week 4.  Bookmark challenge

### Skills

- Designing data relationships using an object-relational mapper
- Designing a database schema
- Manipulating data using the CRUD cycle
- Structuring more complex MVC applications
- Refactoring more complex apps
- Creating user stories

##Requirements

- It shows a list of links from the database
- New links can be added
- Links can be tagged
- Links can be filtered by a tag


User Story 1:

As a time-pressed user
So that I can quickly go to web sites I regularly visit
I would like to see a list of links on the homepage

User Story 2:

As a time-pressed user
So that I can save a website
I would like to add the site's address and title to my bookmark manager

User Story 3:

As a time-pressed user,
So that I can easily categorise the bookmarks,
I want to be able to tag my links.

User Story 4:

As a time-pressed user,
So that I can arrange my tagged bookmarks,
I want to be able to filter my bookmarks according to tags.


Extra story:

As a time-pressed user
So that I can quickly find web sites I recently bookmarked
I would like to see links in descending chronological order

